Results
Alison M. Ashbury, 2022-05-30
“Female orangutans’ DJLs were significantly predicted by an interaction between FAI and fire period, with a medium effect size (β = 0.55, 95% CI [0.17, 0.93]; Fig. 2c).”  (Ashbury et al. 2021)

“The probability of co-foraging between related females was significantly lower during the post-fire period than during the pre-fire period (medium effect size, β = 0.69, 95% CI [0.12, 1.25], Fig 5b).” (Ashbury et al. 2021)

“The model also suggested that rates of aggression may decrease with increasing familiarity due to previous encounters, although with a relatively small effect (Cohen's D = −0.278, p = 0.067).” (Morisson et al. 2020)
